## Database Schema Principles

- Every table has `id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()`
- Every table has `created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()`
- Soft deletes via `deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL` — no hard deletes on user data
- Foreign keys are explicit with `ON DELETE` behavior defined
- No application-level joins that can be a single SQL query
- Migrations are incremental and reversible — every `upgrade()` has a `downgrade()`

---

## Performance Budgets (Single VPS)

| Component | RAM Target | CPU Target |
|---|---|---|
| FastAPI workers (4x) | ≤ 1.5 GB total | Burst to 2 vCPU under load |
| PostgreSQL | ≤ 1.5 GB | ≤ 1 vCPU sustained |
| SearXNG | ≤ 256 MB | Minimal |
| APScheduler + Sentinel | ≤ 80 MB | Negligible |
| System headroom | ≥ 10 GB free | — |

If a new feature pushes a component over its budget, optimize or defer.
